		<DIV ALIGN="CENTER">
		
		<DIV ALIGN="CENTER"><FONT SIZE="+2">Robe of the Lost Circle</FONT><BR>
Zone : South Karana<BR><BR>
<TABLE CELLSPACING = 0 CELLPADDING = 0 BORDER = 0>
<TR><TD><FONT SIZE-="1" FACE="ariel"><B>Added:</B> November 12th 1999</FONT><BR><BR>

This quest is for the <A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/armor_detail.php3?search=213">Robe of the Lost Circle</A>.  You need to be a tailor to do this, and have a large sewing kit. There are four components needed to make this robe:<BR><BR>

<B>1. Needle of the Void:</B> Brother Qwinn in South Karana requires the "Code of the Whistling Fist" and a <A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/quest_detail.php3?search=216">Purple Headband</A>. The "Code of the Whistling Fist" is dropped by Targin the Rock in the Sol B King Room. Returning these items will result in you getting a "needle of the void". <BR><BR>

<B>2. Rare Robe Pattern:</B> Brother Zephyl in Rathe Mountains wants the Idol of Zan Fi, which is in the possession of Brother Raster, who spawns in the Minotaur Elder's room in Lower Guk. Returning this Idol, plus a <A HREF="http://www.loreseekers.com/quest_detail.php3?search=74">Red Sash</A>, results in "a rare robe pattern." <BR><BR>

<B>3. Swatch of Shadow Silk:</B>… is tailored using the following components: <BR><BR>

Shadow Wolf Pelt + Silk Swatch + Scroll of Gather Shadows (low-lvl Necro invis spell scroll)<BR><BR>

<B>4. Scroll of Jonathan's Whistling Warsong:</B>... is bought from the Bards Guild in either Qeynos, Freeport or Kelethin.<BR><BR>

Combining the 4 items (Needle of the Void, Rare Robe Pattern, Swatch of Shadow Silk, Scroll of Jonathan's Whistling Warsong) together in a Large Sewing Kit, will result in the Robe of the Lost Circle.<BR><BR>
</TD></TR>
</TABLE>
